b:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Airtable Automations is best suited for Airtable users, content teams, project managers, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Bardeen, meanwhile, shines for sales teams, recruiters, individual professionals, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2012, Airtable Automations describes itself as \"Built-in automation engine for Airtable database workflows.\" Bardeen, established in 2020, positions itself as \"AI-powered browser automation that runs in your Chrome tab.\" With 8 years between them, Airtable Automations brings the maturity and proven track record of a veteran platform, while Bardeen offers the fresh perspective and modern architecture of a newer entrant."}]]}]
c:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Airtable Automations** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to more features (9 vs 6), availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean Bardeen is a poor choice — far from it. Bardeen excels in its own right, particularly for sales teams and recruiters.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value seamless integration with airtable data, go with Airtable Automations. If runs directly in browser—no server needed matters more to you, Bardeen is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
